12/04/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The appeals chamber of the Court of BiH cut the 20-year sentence of Krsto Savic by three years on Monday (April 11th).
Savic was convicted of war crimes against non-Serb civilians during the 1992-1995 Bosnian conflict in eastern Herzegovina.
The initial sentence was delivered in March 2009.
Savic, former head of the Bosnian Serb police forces in the Trebine region, was convicted of persecuting civilian Muslims and Croats between May and December 1992.
(BHRT, Onasa, Radio Free Europe - 10/04/11)
